  "text": "Images were collected as full 1024 ϫ 1532 pixel arrays, and then were binned down to 256 ϫ 382 arrays. Background images were subtracted from each image in the image cube. The data were then converted to optical density units by dividing the sample data by data acquired from a white reflectance standard using a Beer's Law algorithm. A complete description of this methodology can be found elsewhere [CITATION_1] and in Appendix 1. End of study Bleed, periods during which 10 ml/kg blood was removed (10 min each); postbleed, periods of observation following bleed periods; LR, lactated ringer's solution; blood transfusion, reinfusion of shed blood.",
